HEADWORD: Stumpy
<hw>Stump"y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Full of
stumps; hard; strong.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Short and thick; stubby.</def>
<mark>[Colloq.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧A <xex>stumpy</xex> little man.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>J. C. Harris.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

